  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Ninjutsu (Doton)</p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 9 (Spell Level 5)</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 12</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b> 24 | <b>Successes:</b> 4</p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 12 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 26</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> C, H</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>You make a dome of earth rise up from the ground, trapping targets within. Creatures take 1d3 Chakra damage per round while inside the dome, while you recover 1 Chakra each round you keep the technique active. The dome has a hardness of 8, 45 HP and is one foot thick. A Craft (Structural) (DC 15) or Spot (DC 20) check allows creatures to hit a weak point and deal double damage with their attacks. A Craft (Structural) (DC 20) or Spot (DC 25) check allows triple damage. This bonus can be shared with allies if it can be communicated to them. At the end of each round, the dome regenerates completely.<br><br>Chakra Resistance does not prevent a creature from being trapped in the dome, but can prevent the Chakra damage.</p>\n\n\n\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
